    public class start
extends javax.swing.JFrame
    Start is the connecting page between the cashier and manager screens. It should be opened first so users can see the two options, and when users press the home button on the two other screens, it'll redirect them to this start page.

    • Constructor Detail

      • start

        public start()
        Class constructor to create the JFrame for start. This function calls the initComponents() function to generate the start page based on the design from NetBeans. It also calls the setTime() function to get the current time for dateTimeLabel.
